<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="peach-crisp-mug" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Upside Down Peach Crisp (Mug)</title>

  <p>
    Ingredients:
  </p>
  <tabular>
    <row>
      <cell>2 teaspoons oil</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>2 tablespoons oats (asks for quick oats, soak old-fashioned oats?</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 tablespoon chopped pecans</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
    <cell>1 teaspoon flour</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{2}</m> teaspoon lemon zest</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{2}</m> teaspoon cinnamon</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 peach, chopped</cell>
    </row>
  </tabular>

  <p>Instructions
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          Briefly microwave oil in a 16-oz mug to thin it out.  Stir in oats, pecans, brown sugar, flour, lemon zest, and <m>\frac{1}{4}</m> teaspoon cinnamon.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          In a bowl, toss peach, flour, and <m>\frac{1}{4}</m> teaspoon cinnamon.  Add peaches to mug and microwave until bubbly, about 2 minutes.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </p>

  <p>
    Notes:
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>
          
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </p>
</section>